38 /* Peripheral: AAR */
39 /* Description: Accelerated Address Resolver */
40 
41 /* Register: AAR_TASKS_START */
42 /* Description: Start resolving addresses based on IRKs specified in the IRK data structure */
43 
44 /* Bit 0 : */
45 #define AAR_TASKS_START_TASKS_START_Pos (0UL)
46 #define AAR_TASKS_START_TASKS_START_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_TASKS_START_TASKS_START_Pos)
48 /* Register: AAR_TASKS_STOP */
49 /* Description: Stop resolving addresses */
50 
51 /* Bit 0 : */
52 #define AAR_TASKS_STOP_TASKS_STOP_Pos (0UL)
53 #define AAR_TASKS_STOP_TASKS_STOP_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_TASKS_STOP_TASKS_STOP_Pos)
55 /* Register: AAR_EVENTS_END */
56 /* Description: Address resolution procedure complete */
57 
58 /* Bit 0 : */
59 #define AAR_EVENTS_END_EVENTS_END_Pos (0UL)
60 #define AAR_EVENTS_END_EVENTS_END_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_EVENTS_END_EVENTS_END_Pos)
62 /* Register: AAR_EVENTS_RESOLVED */
63 /* Description: Address resolved */
64 
65 /* Bit 0 : */
66 #define AAR_EVENTS_RESOLVED_EVENTS_RESOLVED_Pos (0UL)
67 #define AAR_EVENTS_RESOLVED_EVENTS_RESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_EVENTS_RESOLVED_EVENTS_RESOLVED_Pos)
69 /* Register: AAR_EVENTS_NOTRESOLVED */
70 /* Description: Address not resolved */
71 
72 /* Bit 0 : */
73 #define AAR_EVENTS_NOTRESOLVED_EVENTS_NOTRESOLVED_Pos (0UL)
74 #define AAR_EVENTS_NOTRESOLVED_EVENTS_NOTRESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_EVENTS_NOTRESOLVED_EVENTS_NOTRESOLVED_Pos)
76 /* Register: AAR_INTENSET */
77 /* Description: Enable interrupt */
78 
79 /* Bit 2 : Write '1' to Enable interrupt for NOTRESOLVED event */
80 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Pos (2UL)
81 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Pos)
82 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
83 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
84 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Set (1UL)
86 /* Bit 1 : Write '1' to Enable interrupt for RESOLVED event */
87 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Pos (1UL)
88 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Pos)
89 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
90 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
91 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Set (1UL)
93 /* Bit 0 : Write '1' to Enable interrupt for END event */
94 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Pos (0UL)
95 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENSET_END_Pos)
96 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Disabled (0UL)
97 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Enabled (1UL)
98 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Set (1UL)
100 /* Register: AAR_INTENCLR */
101 /* Description: Disable interrupt */
102 
103 /* Bit 2 : Write '1' to Disable interrupt for NOTRESOLVED event */
104 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Pos (2UL)
105 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Pos)
106 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
107 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
108 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Clear (1UL)
110 /* Bit 1 : Write '1' to Disable interrupt for RESOLVED event */
111 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Pos (1UL)
112 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Pos)
113 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
114 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
115 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Clear (1UL)
117 /* Bit 0 : Write '1' to Disable interrupt for END event */
118 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Pos (0UL)
119 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENCLR_END_Pos)
120 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Disabled (0UL)
121 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Enabled (1UL)
122 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Clear (1UL)
124 /* Register: AAR_STATUS */
125 /* Description: Resolution status */
126 
127 /* Bits 3..0 : The IRK that was used last time an address was resolved */
128 #define AAR_STATUS_STATUS_Pos (0UL)
129 #define AAR_STATUS_STATUS_Msk (0xFUL << AAR_STATUS_STATUS_Pos)
131 /* Register: AAR_ENABLE */
132 /* Description: Enable AAR */
133 
134 /* Bits 1..0 : Enable or disable AAR */
135 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Pos (0UL)
136 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Msk (0x3UL << AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Pos)
137 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Disabled (0UL)
138 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Enabled (3UL)
140 /* Register: AAR_NIRK */
141 /* Description: Number of IRKs */
142 
143 /* Bits 4..0 : Number of Identity root keys available in the IRK data structure */
144 #define AAR_NIRK_NIRK_Pos (0UL)
145 #define AAR_NIRK_NIRK_Msk (0x1FUL << AAR_NIRK_NIRK_Pos)
147 /* Register: AAR_IRKPTR */
148 /* Description: Pointer to IRK data structure */
149 
150 /* Bits 31..0 : Pointer to the IRK data structure */
151 #define AAR_IRKPTR_IRKPTR_Pos (0UL)
152 #define AAR_IRKPTR_IRKPTR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << AAR_IRKPTR_IRKPTR_Pos)
154 /* Register: AAR_ADDRPTR */
155 /* Description: Pointer to the resolvable address */
156 
157 /* Bits 31..0 : Pointer to the resolvable address (6-bytes) */
158 #define AAR_ADDRPTR_ADDRPTR_Pos (0UL)
159 #define AAR_ADDRPTR_ADDRPTR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << AAR_ADDRPTR_ADDRPTR_Pos)
161 /* Register: AAR_SCRATCHPTR */
162 /* Description: Pointer to data area used for temporary storage */
163 
164 /* Bits 31..0 : Pointer to a scratch data area used for temporary storage during resolution.A space of minimum 3 bytes must be reserved. */
165 #define AAR_SCRATCHPTR_SCRATCHPTR_Pos (0UL)
166 #define AAR_SCRATCHPTR_SCRATCHPTR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << AAR_SCRATCHPTR_SCRATCHPTR_Pos)
